This study evaluates the effects of electronic cigarette use on cigarette smoking and markers of tobacco use, as well as respiratory symptoms and function in smokers with mild to moderate chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

 All participants will receive a 12 week supply of electronic cigarettes to use instead of their regular conventional cigarettes.

